article.headline: Arkansas St. 75, Denver 73
article.story: DENVER -- Donald Boone scored all of Arkansas State's 10 points in overtime to lead the Red Wolves over the University of Denver 73-72 Thursday night. Boone led Arkansas State (11-4, 3-1 Sun Belt) with 27 points and scored two free throws with 11 seconds remaining to give his team the lead for good. The Red Wolves shot 47.7 percent to Denver's 54.2 percent. Junior Nate Rohnert led the Pioneers (6-9, 1-3) with a career-high 28 points and eight rebounds. Brian Stafford had 12 points, and sophomores Rob Lewis and Kyle Lewis each had 10 points. Denver led 59-58 with less than five minutes to go in the second half after scoring seven unanswered points. They trailed by four late in the game but Lewis and Rohnert each scored jump shots to tie the score at 65-65 and send it into overtime.
